text.tspan: Log and Report Information Sessions
The top priority for the dashboard is for Champions to log the
Sessions they run in their community and then report on that
Session so that we know how many Dementia Friends they
have made.
Order the hard-copy materials
Champions also require some physical materials for their
Sessions, for example the Dementia Friends badges they hand
out to attendees. On the dashboard is a simple form for them
to order these materials.
Sign up to requested Sessions
the second priority for Champions is to be able to sign up to
Sessions that have been requested by the public. This involves
them searching for Sessions by postcode and date and then
signing up to say they can deliver it.
Other tasks of lower priority
· Access the online Champions discussion forum
· View and celebrate the number of Dementia Friends they’ve
made so far
· View previous newsletters in the newsletter archive
· View and edit personal details
· View push notifications from the Dementia Friends team
Access and Download Resources
all of the resources that Champions need to deliver their
Sessions (activity guides, handouts etc.) all live on the
dashboard. So it’s really important that they can easily find the
resources they need.
Find contact details for volunteer manager
it’s also important that the Champion can easily find the
contact details for the volunteer manager in case they need to
get in contact for support.
